channel.title: Project Insanity - I need a lot of help
channel.description:
I want to make a ::empty command in commands.java.
I'm using Project Insanity, Exion source.
I also want to add orbs to my client, such as run, health, and the world map.
I want to add a look and feel to my client, instead of Windows jframe.
I want the new tabs, the 474 tabs.
Please, helpful comments. I tried searching too.

item.title: Project Insanity - I need a lot of help
item.dc:creator: @DynastyRSPS DynastyRSPS
item.description:
@DynastyRSPS wrote:

[quote=“I Vain I”][quote author=DynastyRSPS link=topic=476841.msg3491160#msg3491160 date=1296947091]

if (playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("empty")) { c.getPA().removeAllItems(); }

Actually its this;

if (playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("empty")) { c.getPA(0)removeAllItems(); c.sendMessage("You have removed all of your items in your inventory");
[/quote]Are you mentally retarded?
Your code would throw errors.

@All the other questions; client sided.[/quote]
Sorry I’m a noob. What’s the code, because that kid’s code doesn’t work.
